1. Please note new thread #113. Out of respect for this entire site, I suggest we move the brawl &quot;out back&quot; and not make everyone else a party to it.<br><br>
2. Mr. Ramon, you misconstrued a play on words for a racist hit. I was playing with the phrase mano y mano (man to man) and not trying for any type of racist hit at all. Rather it was a commentary on what seems to be what you want, a one on one fight.<br><br>
3. Cook: Nothing, absolutely nothing I can say to you will you consider. That is too bad. A last thought for you, however. I know you love telling us all stories of murder and firefights, and the latest, of capturing a real live Chinese in the bush was noteworthy.  Think about this: Here is an American Soldier, in a foreign land, capturing a Chinese Soldier, in a foreign Land. The American Soldier is there because a corrupt government conned his government into sending him into a land he was not wanted in.  The Chinese Soldier is there because a corrupt government conned his government into sending him in as well.  Chinese in with the North Viet Nam Soldiers, Gosh, what so different that Americans in with the South Viet Nam Soldiers?  My position is still that neither of you should have been there. Neither Communists nor CIA-er's.  Geneva, and the French, divided French IndoChina into two Viet Nams, not the Vietnamese. The USA got had and sucked into South Viet Nam. The North turned to Russia and China, who else did they have given the cold war at the time?  I still say it was a civil war and we, and the Chinese, were wrong for being in it.<br><br>
4. Tom, as usual, calm and clear logic.<br><br>
5. Art. You took my hit well. Good on you.<br><br>
6. And finally, as a general note: Because I was or am a shrink, that does not mean I am &quot;suppose&quot; to be &quot;nice&quot; or &quot;caring&quot; or any other such BS except when I am working with a designated patient.  I hung up my shingle long ago when I entered this site.  Don't expect me to act any different than most of you. I am just a man (not a little commie) for<br>
better or worse. But, as least I take the time to think about all sides of an issue.<br><br>
Now, if you still got bones to pick with me, see at down at #113.<br><br>
